---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SearchBox from '../../components/SearchBox.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Search LSCSS"
    description="Search the LSCSS documentation by problem, topic, comparison, or implementation decision."
>
    <main class="page-shell">
        <section class="site-hero">
            <p class="eyebrow">Search</p>

            <h1>
                Find the CSS decision you need
            </h1>

            <p class="intro">
                Search by problem, pattern, or architectural decision. Useful
                searches include specificity, utilities, state, modifiers,
                legacy CSS, @scope, Tailwind, tokens, and hacks.
            </p>
        </section>

        <nav class="section-nav" aria-label="Search sections">
            <a href="#search-box">Search</a>
            <a href="#start">Start here</a>
            <a href="#problems">Common problems</a>
            <a href="#routes">Quick routes</a>
        </nav>

        <section id="search-box" class="content-block">
            <h2>
                Search the docs
            </h2>

            <p>
                Search for the question you have, not only the page title.
                Try terms like <code>specificity</code>, <code>state</code>,
                <code>utility</code>, <code>legacy</code>, <code>scope</code>,
                or <code>tokens</code>.
            </p>

            <SearchBox />
        </section>

        <section id="start" class="content-block">
            <h2>
                Good starting points
            </h2>

            <div class="hub-card-grid">
                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/what-is-lscss/">What is LSCSS?</a></h3>
                    <p>Start here if you need the short explanation before choosing a route.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/principles/">Principles</a></h3>
                    <p>Read the non-negotiables behind ownership, layers, tokens, utilities, and hacks.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/decision-trees/">Decision trees</a></h3>
                    <p>Use these when you need to decide where CSS belongs right now.</p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="problems" class="content-block">
            <h2>
                Common problems
            </h2>

            <div class="hub-card-grid">
                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/specificity-visualiser/">Why is this selector winning?</a></h3>
                    <p>Check layers, specificity, <code>:where()</code>, and scope before reaching for important.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/decision-trees/">Utility or component?</a></h3>
                    <p>Use practical rules when repeated utility stacks start looking suspicious.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/modifiers-and-state/">Modifier or state?</a></h3>
                    <p>Separate permanent variants from temporary UI behaviour.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/migration/">How do I improve legacy CSS?</a></h3>
                    <p>Contain old styles and improve active work without rewriting everything.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/anti-pattern-gallery/">What does bad CSS look like?</a></h3>
                    <p>Recognise specificity ladders, random values, utility overload, and permanent hacks.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/audit-checklist/">How do I audit a codebase?</a></h3>
                    <p>Review ownership, tokens, components, state, legacy, hacks, and delivery risk.</p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="routes" class="content-block">
            <h2>
                Quick routes
            </h2>

            <div class="hub-card-grid">
                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/examples/">Show me examples</a></h3>
                    <p>Before and after code for selectors, utilities, state, legacy, and hacks.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/comparisons/">Compare approaches</a></h3>
                    <p>Compare LSCSS with BEM, Tailwind, CSS Modules, utility-first CSS, and @scope.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/adoption/">Introduce this to a team</a></h3>
                    <p>Start adoption without creating a rewrite drama or standards document nobody reads.</p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
